A MAN has been arrested on attempted murder charges after he pulled out his gun during and argument with two other people in central KwaDukuza (previously Stanger) on Wednesday and shot them. Provincial police spokesperson Lieutenant-Colonel Nqobile Gwala said the incident took place on Wednesday at 4.30pm on Mahatma Gandhi Street. Gwala said the suspect and both victims were on the street when an argument ensued. “The suspect withdrew his firearm and shot the victims multiple times in the body,” she said. IPSS Medical Rescue together with Alert EMS attended to the shooting. “Two people were treated on the scene by advanced life support paramedics and transported to a local hospital for further care,” said IPSS spokesperson Paul Herbst. Police confirmed that a 37-year-old suspect was arrested at the scene by KwaDukuza police for two counts of attempted murder. The suspect will be appearing in the KwaDukuza Magistrate’s Court on Friday. Last month The Mercury reported that a 30-year-old man was seriously injured when he was shot in the head by an unknown gunman while he sat with friends outside a property in Morningside. Police said it was alleged the victim was sitting outside a Percy Osborne Road property, drinking beers with a friend, when a suspect approached. According to police the suspect confronted the victim and pulled out a firearm and shot him in the head. THE MERCURY